        <p class="style1"><strong>2009 YEAR PROGRAMME   DISTRIBUTED</strong></p>
        <p>As mentioned in the October 2008 edition of our   Newsletter, our <strong>2009 Year   Programme,</strong> with all the <strong>train and   bus tours</strong> listed in monthly order, has been sent out to everyone on   our database. The response and interest shown in the 2009 tours are <strong>overwhelming</strong>. Many experienced and seasoned   train-tour travelers have enquired about a variety of the tours. It seems that   the Namibia train tours are   still very popular in the <strong>&lsquo;upmarket&rsquo;</strong> fraternity, whilst the <strong>Namaqualand</strong><strong> Flowers, Argus</strong> cycle race and <strong>7 Provinces &amp; 3 Trains</strong> train tours are   the early favourites in the <strong>&lsquo;budget&rsquo;</strong> train tours category for   2009.</p>
        <p class="style1"><STRONG><strong>FEEDBACK &ndash;&nbsp;October   2008</strong></STRONG></p>
        <ol>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   The <strong>Motorbike-on-train</strong> tour to the Western Cape and Boland   went smoothly with one biker doing it for the second time!</li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Ons het vanjaar weer met bus, motor en   vliegtuig na die 2008 <strong>Huisgenoot   Skouspel</strong> by Sun City gereis. Mense   het vanaf Kaapstad, George, Port Elizabeth,   Durban &amp; Windhoek ingevlieg om saam met die Gautengers,   asook ander mense vanuit die Noorde van die land, die 40+ Afrikaanse kunstenaars   se optredes te geniet.</li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Die vierde en laaste <strong>Namibiese treintoer</strong> van 2008 het ook weer   by al die lekker toerisme-bestemmings in ons pragtige buurland   aangegaan</li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   The <strong>7   Provinces and 3 Trains</strong> tour has departed and is currently in   progress. Passengers have joined the tour at various places en   route.</li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   A <strong>group of   friends </strong>from Lichtenburg in North   West (mostly professional people) traveled to Cape Town on the luxurious <strong>Premier   Classe</strong> train, hired motorbikes for the   weekend to visit lesser known places and flew back after the weekend.   Lekkerrrr&hellip;.!</li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   The <strong>rugby   train</strong> from Jo&rsquo;burg to Durban, on the luxurious <strong>Premier   Classe</strong> train, for the <strong>Currie Cup final</strong> on the 25th Oct   2008 was organised in &lsquo;quick time&rsquo;. </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="style1"><strong>DID YOU   KNOW?</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   That we&rsquo;ll be hosting <strong>weekend train tours</strong> between <strong>Jo&rsquo;burg and Durban</strong> (Friday early evening to   Monday early morning) in 2009 &ndash; on the luxurious <strong>Premier   Classe</strong> train? It will include one night&rsquo;s   stay in an upmarket hotel in Durban. It&rsquo;s ideal for companies, incentives,   team building, strategic planning sessions, conferences, etc.. More details to   follow soon</li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   South   Africa hosts the largest timed cycle race in the world (the Cape   Argus Cycle Tour) </li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   The world's oldest and largest ultra-marathon (the   ComradesMarathon) </li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   The world's largest open water swimming event (the Midmar   Mile)</li>
          <li>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   South   Africa will become the first African country to host the Soccer   World Cup in 2010 &hellip; and only the second country in the world to have   hosted</li>
        </ol>
        <p>the Cricket, Rugby and Soccer World Cups</p>
        <p>Since the 1940s, South African golfers   have won more golf majors than any other nation, apart from the United   States.</p>
        <p><strong>Budget Tours &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Upmarket Tours</strong></p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>NOVEMBER 2008   TOURS</strong></p>
        <p><strong>Motorbike-on-Train &ndash; Jo&rsquo;burg to Western Cape and   Boland.</strong> This is   the last tour for 2008 for bikers who&rsquo;d like to ride the sweeping corners,   mountain passes and scenic coastal roads of the Western   Cape and Boland, but does not want to travel the 1000&rsquo;s of km&rsquo;s   through the Karoo. 9 &ndash; 15 Nov 2008.<strong> </strong>Give yourself an early Christmas gift.<strong></strong></p>
        <p><strong>Cherry Festival Bus   tour   &ndash; Pretoria and Jo&rsquo;burg to Ficksburg, Eastern Free State.</strong> Enjoy cherries, beautiful scenery, the   Muluti   Mountains and pristine   accommodation and meals. 19 &ndash; 21 Nov &amp; 21 &ndash; 23   Nov (<strong>Both fully booked</strong>)<strong></strong></p>
        <p><strong>Premier   Classe</strong><strong> Train tour &ndash; Pretoria and Jo&rsquo;burg to   Cape   Town.</strong> Enjoy a long weekend end-of-year   excursion to the Mother City on a luxury train &ndash; all meals included.   Stay two nights in a 4-Star hotel and <strong>fly   back</strong>. Two weekends in November: Thursday afternoon to Sunday afternoon.&nbsp;(<strong>Fully booked</strong>)</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>DECEMBER 2008   TOURS</strong></p>
        <p><strong>Cape   Town</strong><strong> Holiday &ndash; Jo&rsquo;burg to Cape   Town.</strong> This tour&rsquo;s popularity is growing in numbers by the   season. We&rsquo;ll be hosting 8 train tours from Gauteng to Cape   Town and currently 6 of these tours are fully booked.</p>
        <p><strong>7 Provinsies en 3 Treine &ndash; </strong>Hierdie 7/8-dag   rondomtalie treintoer raak met elke toer gewilder en voller. Die kuier en   vriende-maak op die toer, met mense wat oraloor langs die roete opklim, maak dit   &lsquo;n uitsonderlike toer. 18 &ndash; 29 December 2008.</p>
        <p><strong>Durban/KZN</strong> &ndash; First week of the December holidays. 4 &ndash; 8 December 2008. (<strong>Fully booked</strong>)</p>
        <p><strong>Good Hope to   Egoli</strong> &ndash; <strong>Cape Town to   Jo&rsquo;burg</strong> &ndash; This 14-day tour will take you on the upmarket <strong>Shongololo Express train</strong> from Muizenberg in   Cape Town to Johannesburg via Worcester,   Swellendam, Mossel Bay, George, Oudtshoorn, Port   Elizabeth, Bloemfontein, Kroonstad,   Ladysmith, Durban, Empangeni, Swaziland, Komatipoort, Nelspruit en   Witbank to Jo&rsquo;burg. Excursions include the Wine Route, Southern Cape, Garden Route,   Karoo, Eastern   Cape, Free State, Battlefields,   Durban and Zululand in KZN, Swaziland, Kruger National   Park, Panorama Route in the Lowveld and lastly   the Highveld. 4 &ndash; 17 December 2008 at R14000 per person &ndash; all   inclusive.</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>A NEW   YEAR!</strong></p>
        <p><strong>Budget Tours&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Upmarket Tours</strong></p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>JANUARY 2009   TOURS</strong></p>
        <p><strong>Stylish tour to   Cape   Town</strong> &ndash; <strong>Premier   Classe</strong><strong> train</strong> and flight back. 29 Jan &ndash; 1 Feb 2009</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>FEBRUARY 2009   TOURS</strong></p>
        <p><strong>Motorbike-on-Train   &ndash; Jo&rsquo;burg to   Western Cape   and Boland.</strong> This   is the first tour in 2009 for bikers who&rsquo;d like to ride the sweeping corners,   mountain passes and scenic coastal roads of the Western Cape and Boland, but   does not want to travel the 1000&rsquo;s of km&rsquo;s through the Karoo. 8 &ndash; 14 Feb   2009.<strong> BMW GS </strong>bikers who&rsquo;d like to   attend the <strong>Nelsons Creek Challenge</strong> at Wellington   should book on this tour. <U><A href="2009_motorbike.htm">More   info</A></U></p>
        <p><strong>7 Provinsies en 3   Treine &ndash; </strong>Hierdie <strong>8-dag   rondomtalie </strong>treintoer raak met elke toer gewilder en voller. Die   kuier en vriende-maak op die toer, met mense wat oraloor langs die roete opklim,   maak dit &lsquo;n uitsonderlike toer. 12 &ndash; 24 Feb 2009. Oud   Spories kan   hul &lsquo;vrypas&rsquo; op hierdie toer gebruik om R800 pp afslag te kry. <U><A href="2009_seven_provinces.htm">Meer inligting</A></U></p>
        <p><strong>Durban/KZN</strong> &ndash; <strong>Jo&rsquo;burg to KZN.</strong> Enjoy a long   weekend <strong>on the beach</strong> and return by   Premier Classe train. 26 Feb &ndash; 2 Mar   2009. <U><A href="2009_Durban.htm">More   info</A></U></p>
        <p><strong>Kruger   Wildtuin &ndash; Kaapstad na Laeveld.</strong> Die Kapenaars kry die   geleentheid om die <strong>KNP en Laeveld</strong> se toeriste-bestemmings per trein en bus te besoek. 27 Feb &ndash; 7 Mar 2009. <U><A href="2009_krugerCPT.htm">Meer inligting</A></U></p>
        <p><strong>Kruger   Wildtuin &ndash; Gauteng na Laeveld.</strong> Die Gautengers kry die   geleentheid om die <strong>KNP en Laeveld</strong> se toeriste-bestemmings per bus te besoek. 28 Feb &ndash; 5 Mar 2009. <U><A href="2009_krugerJHB.htm">Meer inligting</A></U></p>
        <p><strong>Stylish tour to   Cape   Town</strong> &ndash; <strong>Premier   Classe</strong><strong> train</strong> and flight back. 19 - 22 Feb 2009</p>
        <p align="center">*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *</p>
        <p>Contact us now for more details about the   above tours  or click on the <U>More info</U> links above. The majority of these tours   depart from Gauteng.</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>NAMIBIA TRAIN TOUR (Now   from Cape Town   as well)</strong></p>
        <p>This annual and very popular tour over 10 days to our   friendly neighbouring country will again be hosted in 2009 in April and May.   Visits to the Fish River Canyon,   Etosha Pans, Quiver Tree Forest,   Swakopmund, Henties Bay, Windhoek, Omraruru and many more interesting   places are still part of the itinerary on this upmarket train tour. Give   yourself an early Christmas gift and book<strong> NOW</strong> on one of these tours.</p>
        <p>For Capetonians who&rsquo;d like to go on this tour to   Namibia, there is a bus   service available (<strong>FREE of CHARGE</strong>)   between Cape   Town and Upington to join the tour on Day   2.</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>2009 YEAR   PROGRAMME</strong></p>
        <p>Full programme <U><A href="2009_ratesdates.htm">Click   here</A></U></p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>WHY NO HOLIDAY TRAIN   TOURS DEPART FROM PE, EAST LONDON, GEORGE,   etc?</strong></p>
        <p>We&rsquo;ve received a couple of enquiries why there is <strong>no train tours </strong>hosted from PE,   East London, George, etc. The only reason is   that there is no Tourist Trains departing from these cities, except PE to   Jo&rsquo;burg. (And for some reason the Eastern Cape   people don&rsquo;t want to go on holiday in Gauteng!!) We&rsquo;d love to host train tours from   just about everywhere in the country, but the infrastructure (trains &amp; rail   tracks) does not exist. Up to 2006, when we hosted chartered train tours, we did   depart from these cities. Charter trains have been stopped by Spoornet in June   2006.</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>INTERESSANTE   RE-UNIE</strong></p>
        <p>&lsquo;n Groep oud-matriekleerlinge wat in 1972 skool verlaat   het, gaan in 2009 hul <strong>re-unie</strong> op   een van ons Namakwalandse Blomme treintoere hou. Dis nou &lsquo;n &lsquo;rein gedagte&rsquo; om op   &lsquo;n lekker manier weer saam te kuier en saam op &lsquo;n trein te toer. Dit beteken   natuurlik ook dat die re-unie organiseerder ook nie nodig het om&nbsp; hom/haar &lsquo;dood   te werk&rsquo; nie. Geniet dit en kuier lekker saam.</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>POEM BOOK ABOUT the   RAILWAYS</strong></p>
        <p>Echoing Green Press has published<strong><em> Stimela: Railway Poems of South   Africa,</em></strong> selected and introduced by Laurence Wright.&nbsp;The book presents a carefully chosen   popular anthology of forty poems written by many famous poets, including Rudyard   Kipling, Guy Butler, Oswald Mtshali, Chris Mann and Don Maclennan, from the 19th   to the 20th centuries. The poems have been chosen for their popular appeal and   accessibility. <strong>Laurence Wright</strong>&rsquo;s <strong>Introduction </strong>is an informative and easy to   read entry into the collection with helpful and accessible clues to   interpretation.</p>
        <p>The book is available from bookshops   countrywide, and over the internet from<strong> Netbooks</strong> at http://www.netbooks.co.za   or   e-mail books@netbooks.co.za</p>
        <p>Phone 021-551-4248 Fax 021-552-9504,   selling at R140 each. More information available from (Prof.) Jim Phelps at Tel:   035-772-5967 in Empangeni, KZN.</p>
        <p class="style1"><strong>RUGBY at TWICKENHAM, ENGLAND</strong></p>
        <p>The <strong>Springboks</strong> will be playing the <strong>Roses of England</strong> on Saturday,   22nd November 2008, at Twickenham in London. Have you ever dreamed of attending a   rugby test abroad at the RFU head office? Sharing your love for rugby with 86000   singing Poms? Travel with <strong>MakroSport   Travel</strong> on this rugby supporters tour from Thursday evening   20th Nov to Monday morning 24th Nov 2008 @ R15860 pp   sharing (+ airport taxes). Contact JB Train Tours for the detailed Info   Doc.</p>
